# CODEOWNERS — auto-assigns reviewers on pull requests.
#
# Owners listed here get automatically added as reviewers when a PR
# touches their paths. Read the full syntax docs at
# https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositories-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners
#
# Change the handle below to your GitHub org/user handle (or a team
# like @Spwig/core-maintainers) once the org's teams are set up.

# Everything falls back to the core maintainer.
*                       @Spwig/core-maintainers

# Security-sensitive areas — extra reviewer pair worth it.
/core/                  @Spwig/core-maintainers
/accounts/              @Spwig/core-maintainers
/admin_api/             @Spwig/core-maintainers
/payment_providers/     @Spwig/core-maintainers
/cart/                  @Spwig/core-maintainers

# Infra: CI / build / release pipeline.
/.github/               @Spwig/core-maintainers
/Dockerfile             @Spwig/core-maintainers
/docker-compose*.yml    @Spwig/core-maintainers

# Docs — lightweight review is fine.
*.md                    @Spwig/core-maintainers
